4. How .java code compiles and output is shown???
- Computer doesnt understand Main.java file. It needs to be converted to 0s and 1s.
- javac (java compiler) compiles it to form the bytecode (not 0s and 1s something intermediate). It checks the entire syntax as well as structures, if everything is perfect then it forms Main.class file else COMPILATION ERROR...
- java Main -> JVM starts and Class Loader(component in JVM loads file from hard disk to JVM ki memory) loads the main.class file in memory. JVM assigns memory to methods, vars etc.
- JVM finds the main() 
- Executes the entire code.
- System.out is a static printstream object which gets connected to console whenever JVM starts. 
   - printstream cls ka obj banega heap memory mai...out is just a reference to it. stores its address. 
   - System cls ka data member is out which stores objects address, it is marked as static. so out will be stored in class ka METHOD area mai...
- println() prints the text and moves to next line...

